The mesh tongue features a woven Patta tag, and an embroidered Nike Air branding rests on the back heel. Lightweight cushioning is featured by a pre-yellowed polyurethane midsole with a visible Air unit under the heel.

shoeName: Jordan 4 Retro Where the Wild Things Are (PS)
description: The Air Jordan 4 PS 'Wild Things' are shoes for little kids and made for colder weather. It has fleece on both the padded collar and Jumpman icon embroidered tongue. The rest of the upper is built with tan leather and a quartet of color-popped eyelets in neon green, pink, blue, and red. An additional Jumpman logo is featured on the molded heel panel in dark beige and its two-tone foam midsole is supported by an outsole built with gum rubber under the forefoot and heel.

Drawing from an OG colorway worn by Michael Jordan at the 1996 NBA All-Star Game, the Air Jordan 11 Retro Low GS 'Legend Blue' released in 2021. A grade-school shoe, the upper is built with white leather, overlaid by tonal patent leather along the mudguard. Mesh on the tongue provides breathability, while the tongue and heel add Legend Blue to the look. Underfoot, a phylon midsole provides cushioning, giving way to a translucent rubber outsole for traction.

The Dunk Low GS 'University Blue' is a grade-school shoe with a two-tone look. Built entirely with leather, the shoe's upper appears in a mix of white and University Blue, with perforations on the toe box included for breathability. A nylon tongue and padded collar support the fit, while underfoot, a white midsole gives way to more University Blue on the outsole, which sports a concentric pattern for traction.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE 'Royal Black Toe' emerges with classic color-blocking on this July 2020 release. Built with a white leather base, the upper includes Hyper Royal suede over the heel, with black nylon on the eyestay, Swoosh and toe. More Hyper Royal marks the 'Wings' logo, while underfoot, the midsole houses Air in the heel for cushioning. A concentric outsole provides traction while completing the look.

Released in April 2021, the Dunk Low GS 'Michigan' 2021 is a grade-school iteration of a 'Be True to Your School' colorway from 1985. Featuring a University of Michigan look, the shoe's upper is built entirely with leather, finished in a team mix of Varsity Maize and Midnight Navy. Perforations on the toe box provide breathability, while a lightly padded nylon tongue supports the fit. A Midnight Navy concentric rubber outsole offers traction underfoot.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Low Triple White Tumbled Leather
description: The Air Jordan 1 Low 'Triple White' washes out its low-top construction. The shoe's upper is built with a mix of full-grain and tumbled leather for textural variety, with a lightly padded nylon tongue supporting the fit. A Jumpman is included in place of the usual tongue tag, while underfoot, the white Air midsole and concentric outsole complete the monochromatic look.

shoeName: Nike Air Max Plus Triple Black
Nike Air Force 1 Low SP Undefeated 5 On It Dunk vs. AF1
description: Made with the help of the Los Angeles retailer, the Undefeated x Air Force 1 Low '5 On It' released as part of the second installment of the Dunk vs. AF-1 series. Inspired by late 90s and early 2000s sneaker culture, the shoe's leather upper is defined by the Swoosh and heel patch, which appear in blue and red snakeskin, respectively. Tonal suede also emerges throughout, while the lateral heel and orange tongue tag add Five Strikes branding. Underfoot, Air in the midsole offers cushioning.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low White Gum
Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Essential White Black Gold Mini Swoosh (W)
Nike Dunk Low Disrupt Coconut Milk (W)

description: The Air Jordan 1 Low 'Game Royal' sports a classic two-tone look on its low-top construction. The shoe's upper is built with leather, finished in white and overlaid by Game Royal. Perforations on the toe box provide breathability, while the 'Wings' logo has been moved to the heel. Underfoot, the midsole houses Air in the heel for cushioning, giving way to a black concentric rubber outsole for traction.

The Yeezy Boost 700 'Enflame Amber' features a contrasting look between its upper and tooling. The shoe's upper is built with mesh, overlaid by suede and finished in a mix of brown and beige. A tonal toe cap supports the fit, while a hit of blue marks the mesh toe box itself. Underfoot, drop-in Boost provides cushioning, overlaid by an orange EVA carrier, while the herringbone rubber outsole reveals the cushioning unit itself via cutout detailing.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid White Black Light Arctic Pink (GS)
Nike Air Force 1 Sage Low Triple White (W)
description: The women’s Air Force 1 Sage Low ‘Triple White,’ absent of color, focuses attention on the construction of the classic silhouette. Here, the sneaker is retooled in an all-leather upper with a stitch-and-turn build, accented with a tonal Swoosh and heel tab attached by traditional stitching. The upper's pioneering look is enhanced by a revamped platform midsole and supported underneath by an outsole with well-defined teeth.

Originally released in 2010 for a Christmas Day collection, the Zoom Kobe 6 Protro 'Grinch' dropped in December 2020. The shoe's upper features a Green Apple and Volt look, with polyurethane detailing creating a snakeskin-style texture throughout the construction. Crimson on the branding and laces adds to the holiday aesthetic, while underfoot, the midsole incorporates Zoom Air to provide cushioning.

Built for kids a bit older, the Air Jordan 1 Low MMD BG 'Multi Grid' updates the sneaker classic with mismatched colors and geometric prints. It features a contrast-colored grid pattern on the collar, toe, and heel panel, with forefoot overlays covered in blue-on-black microdots. The remaining upper is made from white leather with the iconic Swoosh in Bright Mango. An encapsulated Air unit enhances the cushioning properties of the rubber cupsole, with mismatched blue and yellow rubber outsoles. The laces feature the same hues as well.

Adding a bit of color to a mostly neutral colorway of Kanye West's basketball-inspired silhouette is the adidas Yeezy Quantum 'Amber Tint.' Gold, bronze, and brown tones are featured on the wavy synthetic overlays, which are on a semi-translucent mesh upper. The breathable built has a grey synthetic suede toe cap and a stretchy black neoprene collar and tongue with a molded heel counter that cradles the back of the foot. Responsive cushioning is throughout the full-length Boost midsole with a durable TPU cage and is supported by a herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Retro High CO Japan Neutral Grey (2020)
description: Originally released exclusively in Japan and limited to 2,001 pairs, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG CO.JP 'Tokyo' returned in 2020. Built with grey nubuck, the upper is highlighted by hits of metallic silver on the Swoosh and heel overlay. Nike Air branding replaces the Jumpman on the tongue, while the sockliner sports 'CO.JP.' The inside label on the tongue sports both 2001 and 2020, honoring the two releases.

The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Black Non-Reflective' emerges with an almost-monochromatic look on its signature construction. The shoe's upper is built with Primeknit, finished in black and complemented by a tonal monofilament stripe through the design. A touch of red brings color to the heel loop, while underfoot, a Boost midsole provides cushioning. The TPU shell that overlays the midsole continues down onto the rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70s Ox Black White
Jordan 1 Low SE Crater Black Grey

description: Released in March 2021, the Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Stealth 2.0' updates the 2006 Air Jordan 5 'Stealth.' Built with tumbled white leather, the shoe's upper is highlighted by reflective silver detailing on the tongue and Hyper Royal on the lace toggle and inner lining. Underfoot, the midsole includes visible Air in the heel for cushioning, with the signature shark-tooth detailing contrasting the look in black.

shoeName: Jordan 5 Retro Fire Red Silver Tongue (2020)
description: Released in May 2020, the Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Fire Red' 2020 brings back an OG look for the silhouette's 30th anniversary. Built with white leather, the upper includes a reflective silver tongue and a mesh insert at the quater panel. Fire Red accents emerge throughout, including on the shark-tooth detailing underfoot, while visible Air in the heel provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Flint' 2020 released in 2020 with a look pulled from the late 90s. The shoe's signature overlay appears in blue, accented by reflective detailing. The heel sports Flint Grey suede, while a hologram logo stands out on the ankle. Underfoot, the panther's paw midsole houses Air for cushioning, with a herringbone outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike Kobe 5 Protro Undefeated Hall of Fame
description: Celebrating the Black Mamba's induction into the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame, the Undefeated x Zoom Kobe 5 Protro 'Hall Of Fame' emerges in the colors of the only team he ever played for. Built with a mesh base and underlaid by snakeskin-textured leather, the shoe's upper appears in gold, complemented by a purple Swoosh on the right side of both shoes, with pink on the left. The left shoe also includes 24, 10 and 8 on the pink Swoosh as a nod to his NBA and Olympic jersey numbers, while the tongue and heel include mismatched Kobe Bryant and Five Strikes branding. Underfoot, Zoom Air provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro OG 'Bred' 2019 released to help celebrate the 30th annivesary of the silhouette. Featuring the same OG colorway that Michael Jordan wore while hitting 'The Shot' in 1989, the shoe features a black nubuck upper complemented by hits of Cement Grey. Fire Red accents emerge on the tongue and outsole, while Air in the heel provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 4 Retro PS 'University Blue' is a preschool iteration of the shoe. Featuring a University of North Carolina-style look, the shoe's upper includes a suede construction, finished in University Blue and highlighted by cement detailing that recalls the 'White Cement.' The tongue includes a woven jock tag similiar to the labels on retro Nike basketball jerseys, while visible Air in the midsole underfoot provides cushioning.

The Yeezy Boost 700 'Bright Blue' features a vibrant two-tone look between its upper and tooling. The shoe's upper, built with mesh and suede, appears primarily in blue, complemented by black suede. Reflective detailing on the side wall further highlights the design, while underfoot, the sculpted orange midsole houses Boost to provide cushioning, giving way to a black rubber outsole with a herringbone pattern for traction.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG GS 'Black Mocha' is a grade-school shoe with a subdued look. The shoe's upper includes a white leather base, overlaid by black leather and Dark Mocha nubuck. Perforations on the toe box provide breathability, while underfoot, the midsole houses Air for cushioning. A concentric rubber outsole is included for traction.

The Wmns Dunk Low 'Barely Green' emerges with a pastel look on the classic basketball silhouette. Built with leather, the shoe's upper sports a pale green base, highlighted by Crimson Tint on the Swoosh branding. Perforations on the toe box provide breathability, while underfoot, a two-tone rubber cupsole sports a concentric pattern on the rubber outsole for traction.

The high visibility of the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Yeezreel Non-Reflective' shares Kanye West's unique approach to style. Dropped in December 2019, the iteration is eye-catching in a colorful Primeknit bootie utilizing vivid rope laces, a translucent monofilament streak across the lateral, and a rear pull tab with unusual red stitching. A vivid Tubular rubber sole displays full-length Boost technology for energy return.

One of the original low-top colorways from 1985, the women's Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG 'Neutral Grey' released in June 2021. Built with a leather base, the shoe's upper appears in white, complemented by grey on the Swoosh and heel patch, which are constructed with suede. The usual perforations on the toe box provide breathability, while underfoot, Air in the rubber cupsole provides cushioning. More grey marks the concentric rubber outsole, which offers traction.

Yeezy mixes it up with the adidas Yeezy Slide Kids 'Glow Green.' With fluorescent green vibrately throughout the sandal and EVA foam that makes it longer lasting and light. The simple design strays away from any other branding but the Three Stripes on the footbed. Stay gripped on the ground with horizontal grooves built on the outsole.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Light Bone White

description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE GS 'Brushstroke Paint Splatter' is a shoe built for older kids that embodies the concept of wearable art, as the shoe is made to be similar to an artist's canvas. The lateral side of the off-white textile upper features a black Swoosh that looks as if it was painted on, while beige synthetic suede overlays are enlivened with multicolor flecks of paint. The splatter effect continues on the rubber midsole where encapsulated Air-sole cushioning is in the heel. A black rubber midsole is matched by Jumpman branding on the tongue tag and a Wings logo on the lateral ankle.

shoeName: Nike Kyrie 4 Low Bright Crimson Aquatone
Jordan 1 Mid SE Dark Pony Smoky Mauve (W)
colorway: Barely Orange/Dark Pony-Pale Ivory-Smokey Mauve-Rosewood Grain

shoeName: Nike Dunk High Sail Football Grey (W)
description: The Wmns Dunk High 'Football Grey' brings a neutral look to its retro basketball construction. The shoe's upper is built entirely with leather, finished in an off-white base that's overlaid by Football Grey. Perforations on the toe box provide breathability, while a padded mesh collar and nylon tongue work together to support the fit. A concentric rubber outsole offers traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 QS Valentine's Day Love Letter
Jordan 4 Retro SP 30th Anniversary Union Desert Moss
description: The Union LA x Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Desert Moss' released to celebrate 30 years of the retailer. Bringing back a modified AJ4 created by the two brands in 2020, the shoe's aesthetic is informed by outdoor gear from the 80s and 90s, as noted by its inclusion in the Tent and Trail capsule. Built with a purple mesh base, yellow suede overlays the design, while turquoise on the molded eyelets and heel patch adds further color. Maintaining signature features of its predecessor, the shoe also includes a stitched fold-down tongue, yellow 'UN/LA' tag and translucent TPU wings, while underfoot, visible Air in the heel of the polyurethane midsole provides cushioning.

A follow-up to the 'Limeade' and 'Lemonade' colorways, the Air Max 1 Premium 'Strawberry Lemonade' emerges with a similar style. Built with a mix of mesh and leather, the shoe's upper appears in varying shades of pink, with 'Air' throughout the quarter panel and heel. The tongue tag includes an embroidered strawberry, while strawberries and lemons appear on the sockliner. Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning.

The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS 'Seafoam' is a preschool shoe with a pastel look. The shoe's upper is built with a white leather base, overlaid by nubuck in Seafoam that complements the design. Healing Orange brings color to the two-tone laces, while perforations on the toe box offer breathability. Underfoot, a two-tone rubber cupsole with a concentric rubber outsole anchors the design.

Featuring the same white and black color scheme of the original 'Taxi' release from 1996 is the Air Jordan 12 Retro TD 'Royalty.' Detailed stitching is featured on the white leather upper with contrasting black mudguards in a subtle lizard texture. A metallic gold Jumpman logo can be seen on the tongue, and the lightweight foam midsole is supported by an outsole made up of herringbone-traction rubber pods under the forefoot and heel.

shoeName: Nike Dunk Low Disrupt Dark Green White (W)

description: Bringing back a hyper-limited colorway of James' ninth signature shoe is the 2021 edition of the Nike LeBron 9 'Watch the Throne.' It's named after and inspired by the 2011 album by Jay-Z and Kanye West and made for LeBron and a handful of his close friends and associates. Metallic gold Swooshes shine on the black Hyperfuse upper, fortified with interior Flywire cables and engineered textile wings that resemble carbon fiber. A lush multicolor print is featured on the interior lining and laces, which are partially hidden by ornate gold-plated lace jewels. Matching gold speckles enliven the black Phylon midsole, featuring encapsulated Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot and a 180-degree Max Air unit in the heel.

The Wmns Dunk Low 'Photon Dust' brings a subdued look to its classic construction. Built entirely with leather, the shoe's upper appears with a white base, complemented by Photon Dust overlays, including on the Swoosh branding. The toe box includes perforations for breathability, while underfoot, the two-tone look continues onto the rubber cupsole that anchors the build, which includes a concentric outsole for traction.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Metallic Gold Black White (GS)
description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE GS 'Metallic Gold' is a grade-school shoe with an elevated look. The shoe's upper is built with leather, finished primarily in white and overlaid by metallic gold. The Swoosh and collar contrast the look in black, while underfoot, the white midsole houses Air in the heel for cushioning. A black concentric rubber outsole is included for traction.

shoeName: Nike Blazer Low sacai British Tan
description: The sacai x Blazer Low 'British Tan' brings Chitose Abe's design sensibilities to its classic construction. Built with suede, the shoe's upper appears in Light British Tan, with the dual Swoosh branding sporting both tonal and University Red finishes. The same mix of hues marks the doubled-up laces, eyestays and exposed-foam tongues, with more exposed-foam on the tongue. White rubber overlays climb up from the midsole underfoot, with a herringbone rubber outsole offering traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low Siempre Familia
Jordan 1 Retro High OG A Ma Maniére (PS)
description: The A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 1 High OG PS 'Airness' is made for kids and showcases the Atlanta boutique's updated take on the iconic silhouette. The upper has textured ivory-colored suede with contrasting burgundy accents on the snakeskin-embossed Swoosh and collar. The latter hue is seen again on the woven Nike tongue tag and the retro Wings logo imprinted on the lateral collar. 'A Ma Maniére' script is on the heel overlay. It's built on a cupsole with off-white sidewalls and a burgundy rubber outsole.

The Dunk Low SE 'Free.99 - White' released as part of the Free.99 Pack, emerging with mismatched color blocking. Built with a white leather base, the shoes are highlighted by red, green, yellow and powder blue, with both pairs sharing a brown leather Swoosh. Textile marks the tongue, while the custom sockliner includes Free.99 price stickers. Underfoot, the shared tooling incorporates a beige finished on the rubber outsole.

shoeName: adidas Superstar Bape ABC Camo Green
description: adidas teamed up with the Japanese streetwear brand to create the BAPE x Superstar 80s 'ABC Camo' in May 2021. The shoe's upper is built with leather, featuring a green and brown camouflage print throughout its construction. The mismatched side walls include Three-Stripes on one side and BAPE branding on the other, with a similar mismatched look on the tongues and heel patches. A classic off-white rubber shelltoe leads into a rubber cupsole, which anchors the design underfoot.

The 550 'White Red' brings a classic mix of hues to its vintage basketball construction. Built with leather, the shoe's upper appears in white, black and red, with microperforations for breathability. The woven tongue includes a basketball graphic, with an 'N' logo standing out on the side wall. Underfoot, the rubber outsole, which continues the tritone look, incorporates flex grooves for traction.

shoeName: Nike Dunk Low Pink Red White (PS)
description: The Dunk Low PS 'Valentine's Day' is a preschool iteration of the shoe. Built with leather, the shoe's upper appears with a white base, overlaid by Pink Foam throughout. Dark Beetroot instead contrasts the Swoosh and heel branding, while underfoot, a foam insole is included for cushioning. A two-tone rubber cupsole includes a concentric rubber outsole for traction.

shoeName: Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70 Hi Carhartt Hamilton Brown

description: Originally released in 2006, the Air Jordan 7 Retro 'Flint' 2021 brings back the largely neutral look with this May 2021 drop. The shoe's upper is built with a suede base, finished in Flint Grey and overlaid by contrasting white tumbled leather. The branding adds Varsity Purple to the design, while perforations throughout are included for breathability. Underfoot, the polyurethane midsole houses Air in the heel for cushioning, with a rubber outsole offering traction.

shoeName: Nike Dunk High AMBUSH Flash Lime
description: A fourth collaboration on the retro basketball shoe, the AMBUSH x Dunk High 'Flash Lime' was designed with the help of Yoon Ahn. Drawing from the bright lights of Tokyo, the shoe's upper appears entirely in Flash Lime, built with leather and sporting a perforated toe box for breathability. An exposed-foam tongue, reconstructed collar and Ambush-branded heel counter add to the aesthetic, with a black TPU Swoosh, inspired by motorcycle exhaust pipes, extending past the heel. Underfoot, a tonal rubber cupsole bolsters the design.

A toddlers' iteration of the shoe, the Air Jordan 4 Retro TD 'Lightning' 2021 is a reissue of a colorway that originally released 15 years earlier. The shoe's upper is built with nubuck, finished in Tour Yellow, with the quarter panel and vamp adding contrast via black netting. Grey marks the wings to further contrast the design, matched underfoot by the rubber outsole that offers traction. A white foam midsole is included for cushioning.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid To My First Coach (W)
Jordan 1 Mid Barcelona Sweater Red Patent (GS)
Nike SB Dunk Low Classic Green
Jordan 1 Mid SE Union Black Toe
Jordan 1 Retro High Satin Black Toe (W)
description: The Wmns Air Jordan 1 Retro High 'Satin Black Toe' brings an elevated build to one of the Air Jordan 1's most iconic colorways. The shoe's upper features a familiar mix of black, white and Varsity Red, with the iconic black finish on the toe. Built with a mix of leather and satin, a metal 'Wings' logo appears on the collar. Underfoot, a white Air midsole provides cushioning, with a further hit of Varsity Red on the circular outsole.

shoeName: Nike Air Max Plus Wolf Grey
description: The exaggerated aesthetic of the Air Max Plus TN meets its match in the neutral hues of this ‘Wolf Grey’ variant. Debuting in February 2018, the sneaker sports a tonal mesh upper and midsole, while the welded TPU cage and exposed shank incorporate black into their gradients. The heel boasts a pop of color with its yellow Tuned Air trademark.

In light of the season of the haunting is the Nike Dunk Low Premium 'Halloween.' It features a glow-in-the-dark translucent rubber outsole with an upper of black leather overlays that are covered in tonal graphics that light up when the lights go down. The rest of the upper is constructed from off-white leather with a synthetic leather Swoosh in Starfish orange. The same hue is repeated on the tongue, collar lining, and insole, featuring a creepy-crawly spider graphic alongside traditional Nike branding.

The Air Jordan Mid GS 'Armory Navy' is a shoe available in big kid sizing that injects new energy to the classic silhouette via a refreshed color palette. The leather upper features a pristine white base, dark teal overlays, and a black mid-cut collar. It features a Jumpman icon on the woven tongue tag and a standard Wings logo stamped on the lateral ankle. It's built on a durable rubber cupsole with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning under the heel.

shoeName: Nike Dunk Low Golden Gals Metallic Silver (W)

description: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Natural' brings a neutral look to its lifestyle construction. The shoe's upper is built with Primeknit, finished in a subdued mix of hues and complemented by a post-dyed monofilament stripe on the side wall. No-tie bungee laces support the fit, while the inside of the heel includes Three-Stripes. Underfoot, a rubber cage overlays the full-length Boost midsole, which provides cushioning.

The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Citrin Non-Reflective' dropped in September 2019, featuring a two-tone Primeknit upper that utilizes different weaves for a multi-textured look. The sneaker’s lateral side is marked by a post-dyed monofilament side stripe, offering the design a see-through element. A similar dynamic is at work on the semi-translucent midsole, which reveals full-length Boost cushioning within.

The Air Jordan 6 Retro 'Infrared' 2019 is a 2019 re-release of the OG colorway. The shoe's black nubuck upper includes a reflective 3M layer, with perforations throughout for breathability. The heel, tongue and lace lock sport Infrared accents, with the color also featured on the signature midsole detailing. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning, while the tranlucent sections continue down onto the outsole for traction.

shoeName: adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 Cloud White (Reflective)
description: The Yeezy Boost 350 V2 'Cloud White Reflective' dropped in September 2019, featuring a subtle two-tone finish on the breathable Primeknit upper. Reflective fibers are woven into the knit construction for enhanced visibility in low-light conditions, while a monofilament side stripe on the lateral side adds a transparent element to the lightweight build. The kicks are finished with adidas’ responsive Boost cushioning.

shoeName: Converse Chuck Taylor All-Star 70s Hi Comme des Garcons Play Multi-Heart White
description: A collaboration between Converse and Commes des Garçons, the Comme des Garçons Play x Chuck 70 Hi Top 'Multi Heart' features a series of heart logos throughout the base of the shoe. The canvas upper otherwise appears in white, save for the black strip down the heel. Underfoot, a white vulcanized midsole supports the fit, giving way to a black outsole for traction.

shoeName: Nike SB Dunk High RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 02 Banshee
description: The Gundam x Dunk High SB 'Project Unicorn - Banshee Norn' released as part of a larger collection for the 2021 Tokyo Games. Inspired by the long-running sci-fi franchise, the shoe draws from the RX-0 Unicorn Gundam 02 Banshee, built with black leather on the upper and overlaid by navy leather with a copper trim. The toe box and collar sport angular lines modeled after a Gundam suit, complemented by interchangeable, redesigned Swoosh branding. The lateral heel adds a dark pink unicorn emblem, while underfoot, a concentric rubber outsole is included for traction.

The Air Max 90 'Black White' features a simple look. Releasing for the 30th anniversary of the silhouette, the shoe's upper is built with a mix of mesh and leather, finished in black and grey and contrasted by white on the branding. Underfoot, visible Max Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning, with a waffle rubber outsole providing traction.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 University Blue White
Jordan 1 High Zoom Air CMFT PSG Paris Saint-Germain
description: The Paris Saint-Germain x Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort 'Paris' features a classic colorway with vibrant accents. The shoe's upper is built with suede, finished in off-white and contrasted by black on the nubuck overlays. The die-cut Swoosh highlights the look with reflective iridescent detailing, while the deconstructed collar and 'Wings' logo bring a gradient accent to the design. The heel includes Paris Saint-Germain branding, and underfoot, Zoom Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Barely Orange Light Violet (W)

description: A collaboration between Jordan Brand and Paris Saint-Germain, the Paris Saint-Germain x Air Jordan 4 Retro 'Bordeaux' emerges with an elevated colorway. Featuring color-blocking modeled after the 'Fire Red,' the shoe's white leather upper includes Bordeaux hits on the eyelets, inner tongue and heel. The heel itself sports Jumpman and PSG branding, while Paname appears on the lateral forefoot tag. Visible Air in the heel provides cushioning.

The OFF-WHITE x Wmns Air Jordan 4 SP 'Sail' released as part of a collaboration between Virgil Abloh's luxury brand and Jordan Brand. The classic basketball silhouette emerges with a deconstructed leather build, finished in off-white and complemented by semi-translucent TPU on the eyelets, wings and heel panel. A tonal zip-tie and 'Air' above the visible cushioning complete the look.

shoeName: Jordan 1 Mid Black Racer Blue White (GS)
Nike Dunk Low SE NY vs. NY
description: The Dunk Low 'NY vs NY' gives the nod to the summertime streetball tournament featuring some of New York City's best high school basketball players. Built with leather, the shoe's upper appears in green, contrasted by white overlays and highlighted by orange on the Swoosh and tongue tag. The lateral heel adds further orange via the 'NY vs NY' embroidery, while underfoot, the translucent rubber outsole sports each league and its respective park.

shoeName: Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Essential White Beige (W)
ASICS Gel-Lyte V Kith Salmon Toe
description: To help celebrate the New York retailer's 10th anniversary is the Kith x ASICS Gel Lyte 5 'Salmon Toe.' It was first made available to participants of a Zoom panel that Ronnie Fieg hosted in November 2021. It features a navy and pink color scheme with a pigskin suede upper with a perforated toe box and shite synthetic leather side stripes. 'KXTH' is embossed on the heel overlay with alternating ASICS and Fieg branding on each tongue. A white EVA midsole packs Gel cushioning in the heel.

The Yeezy Boost 380 'Onyx Non-Reflective' emerges with a neutral look on its lifestyle construction. Built with Primeknit, the upper appears in black and blue, with a translucent monofilament window cutting through the side wall. The shoe's sock-like upper is cushioned underfoot by a Boost midsole housed in a semitranslucent rubber cage, with a herringbone outsole providing traction.

shoeName: Nike Dunk Low SP UNDEFEATED Canteen Dunk vs. AF1 Pack
description: The Undefeated x Dunk Low SP features a look taken from the Dunk vs. AF-1 pack. Drawing from the Air Force 1 'InsideOut Priority' from 2006, the shoe's leather and patterned textile upper appears in series of brown hues, with tonal leather piping at the eyestay and forefoot overlay. The Swoosh branding highlights the side wall, while a Five Strikes logo on the lateral heel replaces the 'On Your Feet Kid' midsole graphic of its predecessor. Underfoot, a two-tone rubber cupsole anchors the design.

The Air Jordan 1 Mid 'Purple Pulse' brings a pastel look to its classic basketball construction. Built with leather, the shoe's upper appears in a mix of Glacier Blue and Purple Pulse, with Arctic Punch adding further color to the tongue tag. A classic nylon tongue supports the fit, as does the perforated toe box, while underfoot, the usual Air in the heel of the midsole provides cushioning. A concentric rubber outsole offers traction.
